#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:1
msgid "BPMN Design Criteria"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:3
msgid ""
"This page documents design constraints and conventions that apply when "
"authoring BPMN processes and DMN decisions for deployment in the RONL "
"Business API platform. Following these criteria ensures correct runtime "
"behaviour and prevents issues in the citizen portal and caseworker interface."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:7
msgid "BusinessRuleTask: `camunda:mapDecisionResult`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:9
msgid ""
"A `BusinessRuleTask` that calls a DMN decision must declare how the engine "
"maps the decision output into a process variable. This is controlled by the "
"`camunda:mapDecisionResult` attribute."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:11
msgid "Operaton supports four mapping modes:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:13
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api\\references\\bpmn-design-criteria.md:13"
msgid "Value"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:13
msgid "Returns"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:13
msgid "Use when"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:13
msgid "`singleEntry`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:13
msgid "The value of a single output column from a single matched rule"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:13
msgid ""
"The decision has one output column and a hit policy that guarantees at most "
"one result (`UNIQUE`, `FIRST`, `ANY`)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:13
msgid "`singleResult`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:13
msgid "All output columns of a single matched rule as a `Map` object"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:13
msgid ""
"The decision has multiple output columns and you need all of them as a "
"structured object"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:13
msgid "`collectEntries`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:13
msgid "A `List` of values from a single output column across all matched rules"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:13
msgid "The decision uses `COLLECT` and you need all values from one column"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:13
msgid "`resultList`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:13
msgid "A `List` of `Map` objects, one per matched rule"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:13
msgid ""
"The decision uses `COLLECT` and you need all columns of all matched rules"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:20
msgid "Why this matters"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:22
msgid ""
"The mapping mode determines the Java type stored in the process variable. If "
"the wrong mode is used, the value stored is not a primitive (`String`, "
"`Integer`, `Boolean`) but a complex object (`Map`, `List`). Any downstream "
"expression, script task, or UI component that expects a simple value will "
"fail silently or display `[object Object]`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:24
msgid "`singleEntry` — the default for single-output decisions"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:26
msgid ""
"For decisions with one output column and a `UNIQUE` hit policy, always use "
"`singleEntry`. This stores the raw value directly in the result variable."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:28
msgid ""
"<bpmn:businessRuleTask\n"
"  id=\"Task_AssessPermit\"\n"
"  name=\"Assess tree felling permit\"\n"
"  camunda:resultVariable=\"permitDecision\"\n"
"  camunda:decisionRef=\"TreeFellingDecision\"\n"
"  camunda:mapDecisionResult=\"singleEntry\">"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:37
msgid ""
"The process variable `permitDecision` will contain the string `\"Permit\"` "
"or `\"Reject\"` directly, usable in gateway conditions and script tasks "
"without any unwrapping."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:39
msgid "`singleResult` — structured multi-output decisions"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:41
msgid ""
"For decisions with multiple output columns (for example a completeness check "
"returning `isComplete`, `missingFields`, and `legalArticle`), use "
"`singleResult`. This stores a `Map` as the result variable."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:43
msgid ""
"<bpmn:businessRuleTask\n"
"  id=\"Task_CompletenessCheck\"\n"
"  name=\"Phase 3: Admissibility check\"\n"
"  camunda:resultVariable=\"completenessResult\"\n"
"  camunda:decisionRef=\"AwbCompletenessCheck\"\n"
"  camunda:mapDecisionResult=\"singleResult\">"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:52
msgid ""
"The process variable `completenessResult` will be a `Map`. To use individual "
"fields in downstream tasks, access them by key:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:54
msgid ""
"// In a script task (Groovy / JavaScript):\n"
"var isComplete = completenessResult.get(\"isComplete\");\n"
"var missingFields = completenessResult.get(\"missingFields\");"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:60
msgid ""
"!!! warning \"Frontend display\" When `singleResult` is used, the process "
"variable is stored as a `Map` object. Rendering it via `String(value)` in a "
"JavaScript frontend produces `[object Object]`. The caseworker interface "
"handles this by detecting object-type values and serialising them with "
"`JSON.stringify`. However, to keep process data readable, prefer extracting "
"the specific sub-values you need into separate scalar variables using a "
"script task immediately after the business rule task."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:63
msgid "Known issue in `AwbShellProcess`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:65
msgid ""
"The `Task_Phase3_Completeness` task in `awb-process.bpmn` uses "
"`singleResult` because `AwbCompletenessCheck.dmn` has three output columns. "
"This causes `completenessResult` to be stored as a `Map` and to appear as "
"`[object Object]` in raw variable displays."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:67
msgid ""
"**Workaround (frontend):** The caseworker variables panel serialises object "
"values with `JSON.stringify` before display."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:69
msgid ""
"**Proper fix (BPMN):** Add a script task after `Task_Phase3_Completeness` "
"that extracts `completenessResult.get(\"isComplete\")` into a plain "
"`Boolean` variable, then use that variable in the `Gateway_Complete` "
"condition:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Creferences%5Cbpmn-design-criteria.md:71
msgid ""
"<bpmn:scriptTask id=\"Task_ExtractCompleteness\" name=\"Extract completeness "
"flag\" scriptFormat=\"javascript\">\n"
"  <bpmn:script>\n"
"    var result = execution.getVariable(\"completenessResult\");\n"
"    execution.setVariable(\"isComplete\", result.get(\"isComplete\"));\n"
"    execution.setVariable(\"missingFieldsDescription\", result.get"
"(\"missingFields\"));\n"
"  </bpmn:script>\n"
"</bpmn:scriptTask>"
msgstr ""

